 care— but Israel doesn’t know its master. My people don’t recognize my care for them.”"}, {:version=>"English Standard Version", :text=>"The ox knows its owner, and the donkey its master’s crib, but Israel does not know, my people do not understand.”"}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"The ox knows its owner, and the donkey its master’s manger, but Israel does not know; My people do not understand.”"}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"\"An ox knows its owner, And a donkey its master's manger, But Israel does not know, My people do not understand.\""}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"The ox knows its owner And the donkey its master’s crib; "}, {:version=>" Israel does not know, My people do not consider.”", :text=>"King James Bible"}, {:version=>"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib: ", :text=>" Israel doth not know, my people doth not consider."}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"The ox knows its owner, and the donkey its master's feeding trough, but Israel does not know; my people do not understand.\""}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"Oxen and donkeys know who owns and feeds them, but my people won't ever learn.\" "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"Cattle know who owns them, and donkeys know where their master feeds them. But that is more than my people Israel know. They don't understand at all.\" "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"The ox knows its owner, and the donkey its master's feeding trough, but Israel does not know; My people do not understand.\" "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"The ox knows its owner, and the donkey its master's feeding trough, but Israel doesn't know, and my people don't understand."}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"An ox recognizes its owner, a donkey recognizes where its owner puts its food; but Israel does not recognize me, my people do not understand.\" "}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"The ox knows his owner, and the donkey his master's crib; but Israel doesn't know, my people do not understand."}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"Oxen know their owners, and donkeys know where their masters feed them. But Israel doesn't know [its owner]. My people don't understand [who feeds them]."}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"The ox knoweth his owner, And the ass his master's crib; But Israel doth not know, My people doth not consider."}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"“An ox knows its owner, And a donkey its master’s manger, "}, {:version=>" Israel does not know, My people do not understand.”", :text=>"King James 2000 Bible"}, {:version=>"The ox knows his owner, and the donkey his master's crib: but Israel does not know, my people do not consider.", :text=>"American King James Version"}, {:version=>"The ox knows his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel does not know, my people does not consider.", :text=>"American Standard Version"}, {:version=>"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib; but Israel doth not know, my people doth not consider.", :text=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation"}, {:version=>"The ox knows his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel does not know me, and the people has not regarded me.", :text=>"Douay-Rheims Bible"}, {:version=>"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel hath not known me, and my people hath not understood. ", :text=>"Darby Bible Translation"}, {:version=>"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib; Israel doth not know, my people hath no intelligence.", :text=>"English Revised Version"}, {:version=>"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel doth not know, my people doth not consider.", :text=>"Webster's Bible Translation"}, {:version=>"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel doth not know, my people doth not consider.", :text=>"World English Bible"}, {:version=>"The ox knows his owner, and the donkey his master's crib; but Israel doesn't know, my people don't consider.\"", :text=>"Young's Literal Translation"}, {:version=>" An ox hath known its owner, And an ass the crib of its master, Israel hath not known, My people hath not understood.", :text=>nil}]}